---
import BaseLayout from '../layouts/BaseLayout.astro';
const base = `${import.meta.env.BASE_URL.replace(/\/$/, '')}/`;
---
<BaseLayout>
  <article class="shell py-14 sm:py-20">
    <header class="border-b border-line pb-12 sm:pb-16">
      <p class="eyebrow">Home / Personal research profile</p>
      <div class="mt-8 grid gap-8 sm:grid-cols-[152px_1fr] sm:items-center">
        <div class="grid aspect-[4/5] w-[140px] place-items-center border border-line bg-panel sm:w-full" aria-label="Profile photograph placeholder">
          <div class="text-center"><span class="block text-3xl font-light text-muted">VP</span><span class="mt-3 block font-mono text-[9px] uppercase tracking-[.18em] text-dim">Portrait</span></div>
        </div>
        <div>
          <h1 class="text-4xl font-medium tracking-[-.035em] sm:text-5xl">Vivek Pragada</h1>
          <p class="mt-3 font-mono text-xs uppercase tracking-[.13em] text-signal">Software developer · CS / AI student</p>
          <p class="mt-6 max-w-xl text-base leading-7 text-muted">I study and build software systems that support active human cognition, preserve user control, and work close to the data they organize.</p>
        </div>
      </div>
      <div class="mt-10 max-w-2xl text-[15px] leading-7 text-[#c5c3bd]">
        <p>This site is a working record of that research: the theory behind Active Cognition Computing, the infrastructure it may require, and the projects used to test it in practice. It is part portfolio, part technical notebook, and part map of a larger ecosystem still taking shape.</p>
      </div>
    </header>

    <section class="py-14 sm:py-16">
      <div class="grid gap-7 sm:grid-cols-[170px_1fr]">
        <div><p class="eyebrow">ACC ecosystem</p><p class="mt-3 font-mono text-[10px] leading-5 text-dim">Theory → infrastructure → interfaces → applied systems</p></div>
        <div>
          <h2 class="text-2xl font-medium tracking-tight">A connected research and engineering program</h2>
          <p class="mt-4 max-w-2xl text-sm leading-7 text-muted">Active Cognition Computing provides the primary direction. Each component explores a different layer of the same question: how can software retain meaningful context while remaining legible, local-first, and under the user's authority?</p>
        </div>
      </div>
      <div class="mt-10 border-t border-line">
        {[
          ['01', 'Framework', 'ACC formalizes the shift from artifact-centric software toward systems organized around active context.', 'research/acc/'],
          ['02', 'Infrastructure', 'H-BFT explores human-bounded node authority, unlinkable credentials, and client-encrypted network infrastructure.', 'research/h-bft/'],
          ['03', 'Systems', 'Digital Center, PIL, and Explorer Engine test capture-and-return workflows, derived understanding, and reusable semantic views.', 'projects/'],
          ['04', 'Applied work', 'Semantic Workspace and the AI Systems Institute turn the systems ideas into developer tooling and artifact-based education.', 'commercial/'],
        ].map(([number, title, text, href]) => (
          <a href={`${base}${href}`} class="group grid gap-3 border-b border-line py-6 no-underline sm:grid-cols-[45px_125px_1fr_auto] sm:items-start">
            <span class="font-mono text-[10px] text-dim">{number}</span><strong class="text-sm font-medium text-ink">{title}</strong><span class="text-sm leading-6 text-muted">{text}</span><span class="text-signal transition-transform group-hover:translate-x-1">→</span>
          </a>
        ))}
      </div>
    </section>

    <section class="border-t border-line pt-12">
      <p class="eyebrow">Current direction</p>
      <div class="mt-5 grid gap-6 sm:grid-cols-2">
        <p class="text-sm leading-7 text-muted">The immediate work is to make ACC precise enough to evaluate: define active context, describe what a system may infer, and establish when contextual assistance becomes intrusive.</p>
        <p class="text-sm leading-7 text-muted">The projects serve as test environments rather than finished proof. Their role is to expose architectural tradeoffs and keep the research grounded in working software.</p>
      </div>
      <a href={`${base}overview/`} class="arrow-link mt-8">Continue to overview</a>
    </section>
  </article>
</BaseLayout>
